<p>I want to plot the following function B(r,theta,phi) in spherical coordinates.</p>  <pre><code>Bo     = 1; a      = 1;      % m lambda = 1; % m^-1  syms r theta;  Br = 2*Bo*(a/r)*besselj(1,lambda*r)*cos(theta) Bth = -Bo*(a/r)*diff(r*besselj(1,lambda*r),r)*sin(theta) Bph = lambda*a*Bo*besselj(1,lambda*r)*sin(theta)  [Bx,By,Bz]=sph2cart(Bth,Bph,Br);  x=linspace(0,a); y=linspace(0,a); z=linspace(0,a);  quiver3(x,y,z,Bx,By,Bz) </code></pre>  <p>When I run the above code, I receive the following warning and error.</p>  <pre><code>Warning: Using only the real component of complex data.  &gt; In getRealData (line 14)   In quiver3parseargs (line 87)   In quiver3HGUsingMATLABClasses (line 41)   In quiver3 (line 41)   In taylor_state (line 19)  Error using quiver3 (line 43) DOUBLE cannot convert the input expression into a double array. If the input expression contains a symbolic variable, use VPA.  Error in taylor_state (line 19) quiver3(x,y,z,Bx,By,Bz) </code></pre>